      "content": "Your pain in feeling like your individual efforts are futile is understandable, but the logic that the end is \"already decided\" is actually a common cognitive distortion caused by emotional overwhelm rather than a factual certainty. While large-scale systemic problems feel overwhelming, many experts argue that our collective actions are precisely what steer the outcome away from total collapse or drastically shape what kind of end we face. Please consider speaking with a mental health professional who can help navigate this deep despair and validate your feelings while providing tools to feel less trapped in a hopeless narrative.",
